Londen m. Edmund Warnes
mij last to you was on the p cortt. to which please to be refaned,

I gott abatements in all for you 2 crwnes for which have given y
accct credit. inclosed invoyce for N. 22, which is of the good cheap, &
of which there is about one packett more the rest will be all as now
the marchett aules, in uch I can endeed sake no more ca thes what
I do I have bonght 2 bravce for night rayhes, intended for you
for tryall, oneles I had yd contra order by simes, inclosed also the
acctt of the packett of the stolen goods, theone and the other goeth for
nmeuporte he 21 instant, because wee had no good convyence this
week sence fonded N. 21 of which I have advise that in is well
att nieuporr & ships a surrday last for dover I am glad you
rcc. yd packetts, I hope these will come also sake to yd handes, which
in case give no better incorridgment, will fiustrand my exspectatin
for I assure you I can do noonre

Turnhout m. Geerard de mijn
In antw. aen den ul van gisteren, en hebbe tegenwoodigh geen sergies volgens ul stael, sn
den ul voor dese reijse, daer niet can dienen, heeft ul tijken voor mij gereet laet de

Am mr Sannel de Hulter
alhoewel 13 & 15 deser aen ul hebbe ges. soo hebbe eghter geen antw. becomen, noghtans verhope
dat mijn remises aen ul sijn gewoorden, 't welck magen verwaghte te verstaen. hebbe heden
geertins aen ul connen remiss, faute van oc 't welck soo pnaesten niet en bevinde genootsaecht
sal sijn tot verlies te moeten doen. de wolle wert dagelijck verwaght, sijnde de selve tot austnd
gearriveert, de selve ontf hebbende sal ul wijdere adviseeren
C20 d.
Brujssel m. DRichard Southell
In answer to yd of 15 cur. returne you thanckes for the honour you gave my bill, & for the
trouble you had in grocuring acceptance so the other. as to the concernes of T.V
I have this day peceaved a letder from m. Sabbarton by which be selles mee that he is a
frand that mr. vales things go ils, for my governem., Intrim receave a letter fom m. collier
this there is £200- d more reuming on J.V in 2 or 3 biles of which this day I payd
one of £20- & not haveing monyes to pay any more must suster the rest to buame
for I can not helpt itt, & have no thoughts to redran for londen besides god knows how
many there be more, Ibhn de coninct is imployed ly maynard, he told mee this day
that he would not be to keary upon I.V; butt give time, which of he doth will be
well, butt I doubt others will not, seeng there is so many bills oo severalt handes
I had exspected a prepositm from you about our trade, wee have news again
of a nieuw Intended warr hom france upon is, god in heaven be merei fulle
Mons Kints den 20 april 1682
brussel
Mons in antwort aen den ue van i6 deser ben seer wel te vreden
de waeten noch 14 dagen met het bewijs op annoeet maer daer en
susselen soo ist seker dat het selve als dan noch niet sal betalt worden
ia lightelijck niet in weken want huns hure en is geen wisselbrief
voor mijn deel daer is nu wej ing haen gelegen maer alsoo ick mons baudie
soo lanck heb uyt gestelt voor tgene mjn leste voange hem ad moeten
betalen soo ben daer over wat verlegen en wenste wel dat ul het bewijse
naer hem nam ende het gelt aen 6 houdier geliefde te geeven al wat het oock maer
binnen 6 oft 8 dagen, waer door ul sal veroblig
C28 apll
